 Craig Dunlea is a rugby union prop who was born in Leeston, New Zealand on 2 February 1976. He is a former representative of the Scarlets, a Welsh club who compete in the Magners League, EDF Energy Cup and the Heineken Cup. For the club, he played 30 games, between December 2005 and May 2007, scoring 3 tries.[1] 
